  "text": "A sequence S is called a q-ary modular robust positioning sequence of strength n and distance d, or (n, d) q -MRPS for short, if Next, to construct binary RPS, Berkowitz and Kopparty [CITATION_1] used a short binary string called marker and a special mapping to transform symbols from a large alphabet to binary strings. Their construction then required at least 9d log n bits of redundancy and is reliant on an open conjecture about Mersenne primes. To reduce the redundancy, we utilise another marker sequence and introduce the notion of d-auto-cyclic vectors. Levy and Yaakobi provided the following construction of d-auto-cyclic vectors.",
